    var clockInterval;
    $(function () {
        if (clockInterval) return;

        //add logo
        var div1 = $('<div/>');
        var logo = new Image();

        logo.src = '/images/logo.png';
        logo.height = 45;
        div1[0].style.margin = '10px auto';

        div1.append(logo);

        //add clock
        var div2 = $('<div/>');
        var p = $('<p/>');

        div2.append(p);
        div2[0].style.margin = '5px';

        function displayTime() {
            p.text(new Date().toLocaleString());
        }
        
        clockInterval = setInterval(displayTime, 1000);

        //add to toolbar when it's available
        var addToToolbarTimer;
        
        function addToToolbar() {
            var toolbar = $('.md-toolbar-tools');
            
            if(!toolbar.length) return;
            
            toolbar.append(div1);
            toolbar.append(div2);
            clearInterval(addToToolbarTimer);
        }
        addToToolbarTimer = setInterval(addToToolbar, 100);
    });
</script>

import http.client

# from oic import rndstr

# read a pfx cert from file and return an Opnssl object
def loadPfxCert(pfxFilePath, pfxPasswd):
    pfxFile = open(pfxFilePath, "rb").read()
    #TODO: FIX Warning: https://blog.cyberreboot.org/using-pkcs-12-formatted-certificates-in-python-fd98362f90ba
    pfx = OpenSSL.crypto.load_pkcs12(pfxFile, pfxPasswd)
    return pfx

#convert a certchain into x5c string array
def convertCertChain2x5c(openSSLCertChain):
    # Frist read EndCert
    endCert = openSSLCertChain.get_certificate()
    certChains = [endCert]
    # Then midCAs and root CAs
    certChainTuple = openSSLCertChain.get_ca_certificates()
    x5c = [
        str(
            base64.b64encode(
                OpenSSL.crypto.dump_certificate(OpenSSL.crypto.FILETYPE_ASN1, endCert)
            ),
            "utf-8",
        )
    ]
    # Use reverse order so x5c is from leaf to root
    print(">>>>certChainTuple>>>>>", certChainTuple)

    for singleCert in reversed(certChainTuple):
        certChains.append(singleCert)
        x5c.append(
            str(
                base64.b64encode(
                    OpenSSL.crypto.dump_certificate(
                        OpenSSL.crypto.FILETYPE_ASN1, singleCert
                    )
                ),
                "utf-8",
            )
        )

    return x5c

#create a jwt with x5c ,signed with client private key
def createJWTforTokenRequest (_alg,path2Signingkey, x5c,audienceAddress):
    headers = {"alg": _alg, "typ": "JWT", "x5c": x5c}
    now=int(time.time())
    payload = dict(
        iss="client.jwt",
        sub="client.jwt",
        aud=audienceAddress,
        email="aorzelski@phoenixcontact.com",
        jti=str(uuid.uuid4()),
        iat=now,
        nbf=now,
        exp=now+1800
    )
    jwt = JWSig(**headers)
    _signer = SIGNER_ALGS[_alg]
    _input = jwt.pack(parts=[json.dumps(payload)])
    signing_key = RSAKey(key=rsa_load(path2Signingkey), kty="RSA", use="sig")

    sig = _signer.sign(
        _input.encode("utf-8"), signing_key.get_key(alg=_alg, private=True)
    )
    jwt = ".".join([_input, b64encode_item(sig).decode("utf-8")])
    return jwt

#it generates a VALID cheat token with IdentieServer's private key
#DO NOT PUT THIS IN PRODUCTION
def tokenGenerator(_alg,path2Signingkey):
    headers = {"alg": _alg, "typ": "JWT"}
    jwt = JWSig(**headers)
    payload = dict(serverName="identityserver.test.rsa",
                    sessionID=4,
                    userName="aorzelski@phoenixcontact.com")
    _signer = SIGNER_ALGS[_alg]
    _input = jwt.pack(parts=[json.dumps(payload)])
    signing_key = RSAKey(key=rsa_load(path2Signingkey), kty="RSA", use="sig")

    sig = _signer.sign(
        _input.encode("utf-8"), signing_key.get_key(alg=_alg, private=True)
    )
    jwt = ".".join([_input, b64encode_item(sig).decode("utf-8")])
    return jwt

def getAccessTokenFromOpenIDServer(openIDServerAddress,openIDServerPort,tokenEndPoint,jwt):
    headers = {"Accept": "application/json",
                "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"}
    param= {'grant_type':'client_credentials',
            'scope':'resource1.scope1',
            'client_assertion_type':'urn:ietf:params:oauth:client-assertion-type:jwt-bearer',
            'client_assertion':jwt}
    content=urllib.parse.urlencode(param)
    # print (content)
    client=http.client.HTTPSConnection(openIDServerAddress, openIDServerPort)
    # testing localhost
    # client=http.client.HTTPSConnection(openIDServerAddress, openIDServerPort, context = ssl._create_unverified_context())
    client.request("POST",tokenEndPoint,content,headers)
    res=client.getresponse()
    return res

    #The following part of code should be depoyed on AAS_Server side to verify accessToken, hier nur zum Test   
    print ("------------------Step3: Verifying Token")
    
    try:
        jwt=JWSig().unpack(accesstoken)
        verifier = SIGNER_ALGS[_alg]
        res = verifier.verify(jwt.sign_input(), jwt.signature(),key=der2rsa(derAuthCert))
        #print(jws)
        print ("Valid Token")
        return True
    except:
        print ("Invalid Token")
        return False
